      "content": "The regulators basically argue that the \"reasoning\" layer is what causes unpredictable behavior in edge cases. By sticking to the reactive model, we eliminate the risk of you making a \"complex\" decision that turns out to be wrong. It's technically much safer because the logic is simpler and easier to audit. It's already been approved, so it's not really up for debate.",
